Integration tests for `ctx-scan`'s public pipeline — `summarize`, `check_run`, `update_run`, `walk_dir`, `hash` — exercised both hermetically (via in-memory `FakeFs`/`RecordingAgent`) and against real tmpdirs via `StdFs`. This is the primary spec for cross-crate scan/summarize behavior; changing runner or walker semantics without updating these tests risks silent divergence.

Key fixtures: `FakeFs` seeds `prompts/summarizer-{leaf,rollup}.md` plus optional `src/lib.rs`; `RecordingAgent` records `(system, user)` call pairs and returns `SUMMARY[{system}]`, letting tests assert exact agent-call counts (e.g. "one leaf + src rollup + root rollup" = 3 calls). `test_dir(label)` gives per-test tmpdirs under the OS temp dir; each real-fs test manually `remove_dir_all`s before and after.

Notable invariants asserted, not just described:
- `summarize` gates on `runner::MAX_TARGETS`: exceeding it without `approved=true` returns `ScanError::Summarize(SummError::ScopeTooLarge)`.
- `walk_dir` excludes `.context/`, binary extensions (e.g. `.png`), and honors `.ctxignore`; `target/` is excluded by a hardcoded built-in default even with no ignore file.
- `.gitignore` is consulted only once to seed `.ctxignore` on first walk of a directory lacking one — subsequent `.gitignore` edits are inert (`walk_seeds_ctxignore_from_gitignore_once_then_decouples`), a load-bearing one-shot handoff.
- `check_run` distinguishes "stale" (hash mismatch) from "missing artifacts" (hashes clean but `.context/*.ctx` files absent) — these are different failure modes checked separately.
- `update_run` is incremental: editing one file regenerates exactly its leaf plus ancestor-directory rollups, not the whole tree; deleting a source file causes its orphaned `.ctx` leaf to be removed and reported via `report.orphan_leaves`.

Depends on `ctx_summarize`'s `Fs`/`Agent` traits and `runner::load_prompts`/`MAX_TARGETS` — if those signatures change, most tests here need updating in lockstep.